{"lemma":"مِطْرَفَيْ","slug":"مِطْرَفَيْ","root":"ط.ر.ف","root_slug":"ط-ر-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ط-ر-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n26631","n26632","n26633","n26634","n26635","n26636","n26639"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%90%D8%B7%D9%92%D8%B1%D9%8E%D9%81%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n26631","headword_ar":"مَطْرَفٌ","root":"Trf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miTorafN","text_ar":"مِطْرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ―         -b2-  and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyfN","text_ar":"طَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26632","headword_ar":"مُطْرَفٌ","root":"Trf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miTorafN","text_ar":"مِطْرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTorifN","text_ar":"مُطْرِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and see also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyfN","text_ar":"طَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26633","headword_ar":"مُطْرِفٌ","root":"Trf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[act. part. n. of 4, q. v.]. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^ano$idi Albayotayoni","text_ar":"اَنْشِدِ البَيْتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuTorifayoni","text_ar":"المُطْرِفَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", a phrase used by El-Hareeree, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Recite thou the two verses that adduce what is strange,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extraordinary, and approved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deemed good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some relate it, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuTorafayoni","text_ar":"المُطْرَفَيْنِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", expl. by Mtr as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are ornamented at their two extremities;"},{"kind":"text","text":"like the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ridaA='","text_ar":"رِدَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muToraf","text_ar":"مُطْرَف"},{"kind":"text","text":": or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuTar~afayoni","text_ar":"المُطَرَّفَيْنِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning, if correctly related,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are beautified, and excite admiration, in the first and last foot;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened to the horse termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTar~afN","text_ar":"مُطَرَّفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", that is white in the head and the tail: and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmTr~fyn","text_ar":"المطرّفين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmuTar~afayoni","text_ar":"المُطَرَّفَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] may mean"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmstTrfyn","text_ar":"المستطرفين"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmusotaTorafayoni","text_ar":"المُسْتَطْرَفَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (Har p. 615: in the next p. of which, an ex. is given.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyfN","text_ar":"طَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n26634","headword_ar":"مِطْرَفٌ","root":"Trf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, L, Msb, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTorafN","text_ar":"مُطْرَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, L, Msb, K, TA,) the latter, only, mentioned in the K, (TA,) and this is the original form, because it is from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTorifa","text_ar":"اَطْرِفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", but the dammeh was deemed difficult of pronunciation, and therefore kesreh was substituted for it, (Fr, S, O, TA,) like as is the case in"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miSoHafN","text_ar":"مِصْحَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (Fr, TA,) and IAth mentions also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTorafN","text_ar":"مَطْرَفٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A garment,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb,) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as is termed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ridaA='","text_ar":"رِدَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the kind of cloth called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaz~","text_ar":"خَزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"square,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four-sided,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having ornamental"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"coloured"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"figured, borders"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEolaAm","text_ar":"اَعْلَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (S, O, Msb, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a garment having, in its two ends,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sides,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY Tarafayohi","text_ar":"فِى طَرَفَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two such borders"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EalamaAni","text_ar":"عَلَمَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"): (Fr, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a square,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"four-sided, garment of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaz~","text_ar":"خَزّ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTaArifu","text_ar":"مَطَارِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, O, Msb, K.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maTaArifu","text_ar":"مَطَارِفُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also applied to (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Clouds"},{"kind":"text","text":"[as being likened to the garments thus called]. (TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dkn","text_ar":"دكن"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyfN","text_ar":"طَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","O","L","Msb","TA","K","Fr"]},{"entry_id":"n26635","headword_ar":"مُطَرَّفٌ","root":"Trf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white in the head and the tail, the rest of him being of a different colour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and in like manner"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black in the head and the tail."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K.) And, accord. to AO,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^abolaqu muTar~afN","text_ar":"اَبْلَقُ مُطَرَّفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A horse"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white in the head:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and likewise"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white in the tail and the head."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aApN muTar~afapN","text_ar":"شَاةٌ مُطَرَّفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"A sheep or goat"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black in the end of the tail, in other parts white:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"white in the ends of the ears, and for the rest part black:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"black in the ends of the ears, and for the rest part white."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTorifN","text_ar":"مُطْرِفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sajoEN","text_ar":"سَجْعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  In a verse of Sá'ideh the Hudhalee, as some relate it, but accord. to others it is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTar~if","text_ar":"مُطَرِّف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.], (O, TA,) describing a horse, (O,) it signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"murad~adN fiY Alkarami","text_ar":"مُرَدَّدٌ فِى الكَرَمِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Repeatedly improved in generosity by descent from a number of generous sires and dams"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (O, TA.) ―         -b4-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"musotaTurafN","text_ar":"مُسْتَطُرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n26636","headword_ar":"مُطَرِّفٌ","root":"Trf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who fights around the army:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K, TA: [see 2, second sentence:]) or, as some say,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who fights the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aToraAf","text_ar":"اَطْرَاف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noble,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exalted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TarafN","text_ar":"طَرَفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"q. v., or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TirofN","text_ar":"طِرْفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of men."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-  In a verse of Sá'ideh the Hudhalee, (O, TA,) describing a horse, (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that repels those that form the side,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"flank, of the horses and of the"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"hostile"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"company of men:"},{"kind":"text","text":"but as some relate it, the word is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muTar~af","text_ar":"مُطَرَّف"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (O, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["O","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n26639","headword_ar":"مُطَّرَفٌ","root":"Trf","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A camel"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"newly purchased:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"or purchased from another part of the country, and therefore yearning for his accustomed place."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IB, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["S"]}]}}